We do not yet have a web based access to warnings (e.g. through a Hudson 
&lt;https://hudson.dev.java.net/&gt; build) but we may do so eventually. In 
the mean time, if you have installed FindBugs 
&lt;http://findbugs.sourceforge.net/&gt;, you can view the warnings locally on 
your computer. Simply download the analysis file at:

http://findbugs.cs.umd.edu/cloud/heritrix/index.xml.gz

and unzip and open it in FindBugs.

Thanks,
Nat


On 4/13/2010 3:28 PM, Gordon Mohr wrote:
&gt; Is there a way to review the list of warnings without accepting an 
&gt; (unsigned, requests-access-to-my-computer) Java WebStart application?
&gt;
&gt; Given the recent spate of development-resource-site compromises 
&gt; (Atlassian, Apache), and (separately) security issues with Java 
&gt; applet/webstart sandboxing  in versions up to (and perhaps including) 
&gt; 1.6.0_19, I prefer plain web access for light info review.
&gt;
&gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;
&gt; On 4/13/10 11:49 AM, Nat Ayewah wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Hello,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; I am a PhD student working with the FindBugs project, at the University
&gt;&gt; of Maryland. FindBugs &lt;http://findbugs.sourceforge.net/&gt; is a popular
&gt;&gt; open source static analysis tool that can analyze Java software and
&gt;&gt; identify bugs. We recently analyzed *Heritrix*, and identified about 42
&gt;&gt; warnings that might be of interest to the project. You can launch an
&gt;&gt; instance of FindBugs and evaluate each warning using this link (requires
&gt;&gt; Java): http://findbugs.cs.umd.edu/cloud/heritrix.jnlp (You may also
&gt;&gt; comment on any warning by signing into a Google, Yahoo or OpenID 
&gt;&gt; account)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; FindBugs has recently started a community review of several open source
&gt;&gt; projects. This is similar to a recently completed review
&gt;&gt; &lt;http://findbugs.sourceforge.net/&gt; at Google in which almost 300
&gt;&gt; engineers reviewed thousands of issues, fixing many of them. I would
&gt;&gt; like to invite you all to participate in the review for Heritrix, and
&gt;&gt; other open source projects. During the review, you are able to comment
&gt;&gt; on each warning and evaluate it as &quot;Must Fix&quot;, &quot;Mostly Harmless&quot;, &quot;Not a
&gt;&gt; Bug&quot; and other classifications. We are particularly interested in
&gt;&gt; learning if any warnings are causing problems in production.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The list of projects currently included in our review is at
&gt;&gt; http://findbugs.cs.umd.edu/cloud/
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Thanks in advance for your consideration.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Kind regards,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Nat Ayewah
&gt;&gt; PhD candidate, University of Maryland
&gt;&gt; http://www.cs.umd.edu/~ayewah
&gt;&gt; ayewah@...
&gt;&gt;
